    "The Web of Science (WoS) database, which is considered one of the most prestigious academic databases in operation up to date, recorded the growing number of publications related to sustainable education from mere in 1991 to 4055 in 2022.",
    "Our paper focuses on sustainable education at HEIs during and after the COVID-19 pandemic via conducting a thorough and structured bibliometric review study and deriving results for practitioners and academics.",
    "Literature ReviewThe recent COVID-19 pandemic has acted as a catalyst for radical transformations in higher education approaches, creating an urgent need for digital transformation [28].",
    "The global coronavirus outbreak has forced universities to move their training processes and distance learning online, leading to the emergence of insightful webinars conducted by higher education experts [29; 30].",
    "This shift has highlighted the innate technological capabilities of universities, enabling them to deliver good teaching with relative ease."
